  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">This retraction note addresses the publication titled \"Characterization of brown rust resistance in bread wheat using yield related morphological indices,\" originally published in Genetic Resources and Crop Evolution in 2026. The lack of citations and community engagement following the retraction indicates a significant level of controversy surrounding the work, leading to critical discourse in the scientific community.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The publication \"Characterization of brown rust resistance in bread wheat using yield related morphological indices\" has been retracted, which inherently invites scrutiny and critical discourse among researchers. This retraction, noted in the journal Genetic Resources and Crop Evolution, hints at underlying issues with the methodology or findings that necessitated such a significant step.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Given the absence of citations, it is clear that the work has not gained traction within the academic community, highlighting the challenges that can arise when research does not meet the rigorous standards expected in scientific investigation. The key institutions involved, including the European University of Lefke and King Saud University, generally uphold strong research standards, suggesting that this particular study may have faced particular challenges or controversies that led to its retraction.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The lack of online mentions or community discourse further indicates a limited impact or engagement with the study. Without discussions on platforms such as Wikipedia or Reddit, the work appears to have not resonated with either the academic community or the public, a situation that often accompanies publications that face retraction.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">This retraction serves as a reminder of the complexities inherent in publishing scientific research, as well as the importance of robust peer review and transparent data sharing. While the authors from diverse institutions such as the Cotton Research Institute and the Chinese Academy of Agricultural Sciences may have intended to contribute to the field, the circumstances surrounding this publication reflect the critical importance of maintaining integrity and rigorous standards in scholarly communications.</p>",
